        "description": "Quantitative comparison metric E% computed for all QoIs at all operating points. Validation uncertainty Uval estimated per ASME V&V 20. Acceptance: |E%| < Uval for ≥80% of operating points. Achieved: 5/5 NIH points within Uval; 47/48 velocity comparison points within Uval. Pass."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is directly the clinical decision variable — absolute hemolysis below 0.01 g/100 L threshold. Secondary QoIs (velocity field, wall shear stress) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis via the power-law damage model. The validation experiment measured NIH directly using the same power-law accumulation method.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
